 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="o">1</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">The regime of dynamic response to an internal rapid energy release (\Delta t \lesssim t_{\text{diff}}) in a not too hot star (T_{\text{h}}\lesssim 10^9\ \text{K}). It is characterized by a rather rapid rise and longer decay on diffusion time-scales \Delta t_{\text{s}}\sim t_{\text{diff}}. The peak of the surface emission weakly depends on \Delta t</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="o">2</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">The regime of quasi-stationary response in a not too hot star (T_{\text{h}}\lesssim 10^9\ \text{K}) to a slow energy release (\Delta t \gtrsim t_{\text{diff}}). It produces a peak of the surface emission which resembles the internal energy release, lasts for \sim \Delta t, and weakly depends on t_{\text{diff}}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="o">3</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">The regime of efficient neutrino cooling of the heater in a hot star (T_{\text{h}}\gtrsim 10^9\ \text{K}). It leads to weak variations of the surface emission</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
